" Typography.StylisticSet14=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet15=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet16=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet17=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet18=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet19=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet20=\"False\" Typography.Fraction=\"Normal\" Typography.SlashedZero=\"False\" Typography.MathematicalGreek=\"False\" Typography.EastAsianExpertForms=\"False\" Typography.Variants=\"Normal\" Typography.Capitals=\"Normal\" Typography.NumeralStyle=\"Normal\" Typography.NumeralAlignment=\"Normal\" Typography.EastAsianWidths=\"Normal\" Typography.EastAsianLanguage=\"Normal\" Typography.StandardSwashes=\"0\" Typography.ContextualSwashes=\"0\" Typography.StylisticAlternates=\"0\"><Paragraph FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontSize=\"16\" Margin=\"0,0,0,10.67\"><Run>Gabriel Garcia Moreno was first elected to the </Run><Span><Run>presidency </Run></Span><Run>of Ecuador in 1861, and then twice after that. Besides restoring higher education and a good economy to his country, he made it a Catholic State in accordance with the Church\'s social teachings. His policies incurred the hatred of his enemies in his own government, the Freemasons, who brutally assassinated him in 1875.</Run></Paragraph></Section>',2,NULL),('Geom-Classical',138,'Classical Geometry',NULL,NULL,4,NULL),('HeartEurope',58,'\"A Heart for Europe\" - the story of the Last Holy Roman Emperor','Course subtitle not defined ','<Section xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation\" xml:space=\"preserve\" TextAlignment=\"Left\" LineHeight=\"Auto\" IsHyphenationEnabled=\"False\" xml:lang=\"en-us\" FlowDirection=\"LeftToRight\" NumberSubstitution.CultureSource=\"Text\" NumberSubstitution.Substitution=\"AsCulture\" FontFamily=\"Segoe UI\" FontStyle=\"Normal\" FontWeight=\"Normal\" FontStretch=\"Normal\" FontSize=\"12\" Foreground=\"#FF000000\" Typography.StandardLigatures=\"True\" Typography.ContextualLigatures=\"True\" Typography.DiscretionaryLigatures=\"False\" Typography.HistoricalLigatures=\"False\" Typography.AnnotationAlternates=\"0\" Typography.ContextualAlternates=\"True\" Typography.HistoricalForms=\"False\" Typography.Kerning=\"True\" Typography.CapitalSpacing=\"False\" Typography.CaseSensitiveForms=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet1=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet2=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet3=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet4=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet5=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet6=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet7=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet8=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet9=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet10=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet11=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet12=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet13=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet14=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet15=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet16=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet17=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet18=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet19=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet20=\"False\" Typography.Fraction=\"Normal\" Typography.SlashedZero=\"False\" Typography.MathematicalGreek=\"False\" Typography.EastAsianExpertForms=\"False\" Typography.Variants=\"Normal\" Typography.Capitals=\"Normal\" Typography.NumeralStyle=\"Normal\" Typography.NumeralAlignment=\"Normal\" Typography.EastAsianWidths=\"Normal\" Typography.EastAsianLanguage=\"Normal\" Typography.StandardSwashes=\"0\" Typography.ContextualSwashes=\"0\" Typography.StylisticAlternates=\"0\"><Paragraph><Run FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontSize=\"16\">This is the little known story of how the last Catholic Holy Roman Emperor, Charles of Austria, was unjustly ousted from his land and people in World War I. Ignoring his constant pleas for </Run><Run FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontSize=\"16\">peace, the other powers continued the war. At the end, the Allies stablished a revolutionary dominion in Austria according to their own designs, in place of Charles\' peaceful regime. Charles was exiled to Madeira and there died.</Run></Paragraph></Section>',1,NULL),('Hist-SouthAmer',67,'South and Central American Geography and History','Course subtitle not defined',NULL,2,NULL),('Hist-US',65,'United States History for High School ','','<Section xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation\" xml:space=\"preserve\" TextAlignment=\"Left\" LineHeight=\"Auto\" IsHyphenationEnabled=\"False\" xml:lang=\"en-us\" FlowDirection=\"LeftToRight\" NumberSubstitution.CultureSource=\"Text\" NumberSubstitution.Substitution=\"AsCulture\" FontFamily=\"Segoe UI\" FontStyle=\"Normal\" FontWeight=\"Normal\" FontStretch=\"Normal\" FontSize=\"12\" Foreground=\"#FF000000\" Typography.StandardLigatures=\"True\" Typography.ContextualLigatures=\"True\" Typography.DiscretionaryLigatures=\"False\" Typography.HistoricalLigatures=\"False\" Typography.AnnotationAlternates=\"0\" Typography.ContextualAlternates=\"True\" Typography.HistoricalForms=\"False\" Typography.Kerning=\"True\" Typography.CapitalSpacing=\"False\" Typography.CaseSensitiveForms=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet1=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet2=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet3=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet4=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet5=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet6=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet7=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet8=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet9=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet10=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet11=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet12=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet13=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet14=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet15=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet16=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet17=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet18=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet19=\"False\" Typography.StylisticSet20=\"False\" Typography.Fraction=\"Normal\" Typography.SlashedZero=\"False\" Typography.MathematicalGreek=\"False\" Typography.EastAsianExpertForms=\"False\" Typography.Variants=\"Normal\" Typography.Capitals=\"Normal\" Typography.NumeralStyle=\"Normal\" Typography.NumeralAlignment=\"Normal\" Typography.EastAsianWidths=\"Normal\" Typography.EastAsianLanguage=\"Normal\" Typography.StandardSwashes=\"0\" Typography.ContextualSwashes=\"0\" Typography.StylisticAlternates=\"0\"><Paragraph><Run FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontSize=\"16\">This whole course tells the history of the U.S. up to the turn of the century from an unabashedly Catholic standpoint. It begins with Columbus\' discovery of America, traces out the work and culture of the Catholic Spanish and French, setting that in contrast with the mostly Protestant English. The whole founding and growth of our country is enriched with real quotes from key figures, and everything is judged under the light of Catholic social teaching. The book marks out the constant struggle between Catholicism and atheism as it has been experienced in the U.S. Throughout the book, we especially feature various smaller details left out by other history textbooks, which particularly underscore central ideas. </Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontSize=\"16\">We bluntly give our </Run><Run FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontWeight=\"Bold\" FontSize=\"16\">interpretation </Run><Run FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontSize=\"16\">and </Run><Run FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontWeight=\"Bold\" FontSize=\"16\">critique </Run><Run FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontSize=\"16\">of the historical events at intervals throughout the text, marked off with a different font from the rest of the text. The student will not be tested on these parts but is encouraged to read them.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontFamily=\"Times New Roman\" FontSize=\"16\">Part 1 of the history course covers up to the Civil War.</Run></Paragraph></Section>',4,NULL),('Iliad',113,'\"The Iliad\"','','<Section xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation\" xml:space=\"preserve\" TextAlignment=\"Left\" LineHeight=\"Auto\" IsHyphenationEnabled=\"False\" xml:lang=\"en-us\" FlowDirection=\"LeftToRight\" Numb